  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves trying to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Money laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in significant legal penalties, including:\n\n1. Hefty fines\n2. Prison sentences\n3. Seizure of assets\n4. Criminal record\n\nThe process typically involves three stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into the financial system)\n- Layering (concealing the source of the money through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making the money appear legitimate)\n\nLaw enforcement and financial institutions have many tools to detect and prevent money laundering.",
